<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"line-height:14.4pt"><span style=3D"font-fam=
ily:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;;color:#666666">By&nbsp;<span style=3D"text-t=
ransform:uppercase"><a href=3D"http://www.politico.com/staff/daniel-strauss=
" target=3D"_top"><b><span style=3D"color:#666666;text-decoration:none">DAN=
IEL
 STRAUSS</span></b></a></span><o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;;color:black">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;;color:black">Bernie Sanders is accusing Democratic National Committee cha=
irwoman Debbie Wasserman Schultz of trying to tip the party convention in H=
illary Clinton's favor, saying the chairwoman
 has packed the committees with Clinton supporters.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;;color:black">In a&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://www.politico.com/f/?id=3D0000015=
4-86bf-da04-a3ff-9ebfd97e0000" target=3D"_blank"><span style=3D"color:#0A7C=
C4;text-decoration:none">letter</span></a>&nbsp;to the chairwoman,
 the Sanders noted that of the 45 names he submitted Democratic National Co=
nvention committees, Wasserman Schultz appointed only three.<o:p></o:p></sp=
an></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;;color:black"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;;color:black">&quot;I believe the composition of the standing committees m=
ust reflect the relative support that has been received by both campaigns,&=
quot; Sanders wrote in the letter dated May 6. &quot;That was
 why I was so disappointed to learn that of the over forty people our campa=
ign submitted at your request you chose to select only three of my recommen=
dations for the three standing committees. Moreover, you did not assign eve=
n on of the people submitted by
 our campaign to the very important Rules Committee of the Democratic Natio=
nal Convention.&quot;<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;;color:black"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;;color:black">Sanders said that if the disagreement over convention commit=
tee appointments is not resolved, he would have his delegates move to chang=
e the platform on the floor of the convention.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;;color:black"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;;color:black">&quot;It is my hope we can quickly resolve this in a fair wa=
y,&quot; Sanders wrote. &quot;If the process is set up to produce an unfair=
, one-sided result, we are prepared to mobilize our delegates
 to force as many votes as necessary to amend the platform and rules of the=
 floor convention.&quot;<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;;color:black"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;;color:black">Sanders' chances of taking the Democratic nomination have gr=
own, as he has a deep disadvantage in both pledged and superdelegates. But =
the insurgent candidate has vowed to continue
 on, and his deep run into the primary gives him additional leverage to pul=
l the party to the left.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;;color:black"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;;color:black">In his letter, Sanders also mentioned the Democratic Party p=
latform drafting committee. In the letter he recounted Wasserman Schultz ha=
d discussed changing the process for selecting
 members of the committee.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;;color:black"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;;color:black">&quot;In our conversation, you told me with respect to the p=
latform Drafting Committee that you would consider allowing each campaign t=
o submit ten names from which you would choose four
 from each and then you would add an additional seven,&quot; Sanders contin=
ued. &quot;While having four members on the Drafting Committee is an improv=
ement, it does not address the fact that up to this point Bernie 2016 has s=
ecured 45% of the pledged delegates awarded.
 Frankly, we believe that percentage will go up in the coming weeks and, of=
 course, we hope it will end up being a majority.&quot;<o:p></o:p></span></=
p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;;color:black"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;;color:black">Sanders argued that each campaign should be able to pick sev=
en members for the committee with the fifteenth member being one picked by =
both campaigns.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;;color:black"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;;color:black">&quot;This process will also ensure that the chairs of the s=
tanding committees conduct their proceedings with fairness and transparency=
,&quot; Sanders argued.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;;color:black">In its response to Sanders letter, the DNC released a statem=
ent saying both campaigns would be represented at the convention.<o:p></o:p=
></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;;color:black"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;;color:black">&quot;Because the Party=92s platform is a statement of our v=
alues, the DNC is committed to an open, inclusive and representative proces=
s,&quot; the DNC said in a statement. &quot;Both of our campaigns
 will be represented on the Drafting Committee, and just as we did in 2008 =
and 2012, the public will have opportunities to participate&quot;<br>
